examples.en: He ruined the family's good name.
Our grandfather was the family's patriarch.
Our grandmother was the family's matriarch.
His job is the family's main source of income.
She is the repository of her family's history.
His actions sort ill with his family's wishes.
Her patrimony was the family's newspaper business.
She works to provide for her family's basic needs.
He was prepared to fight to defend his family's honor.
His family's name gives him a lot of pull in this town.
He was considered the redeemer of the family's reputation.
I felt I was being shut out from all the family's affairs.
In spite of her family's opinion, she fetched up the winner.
The house has been in the family's possession since the 1500s.
In your family's eyes, she sniffled, I'm not good enough.
Their knowledge of the family's history extends back to colonial times.
The family's philanthropy made it possible to build the public library.
A serious accident can have a dramatic effect on your family's finances.
The family's fortune waned and they could not keep their household staff.
He was a whoring, drunken scapegrace who was blackening the family's name.
...he's been the family's foremost reliance in times of trouble many times...
I'm sorry to hear of your family's sad loss (=the death of someone you love).
The family's theory was that the cheating businessmen somehow framed their brother.
The family's cat did an exemplary job of keeping the house and yard free of all rodents.
My family's scattered over hell and half of Georgia. *
